    {
      "id": "node-primitive-note-composition",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Composition Decisions So Far",
      "position": {
        "x": 640,
        "y": 1784
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Composition Decisions So Far\n\n- content + ports: **allowed**\n- content + controls: **allowed**\n- default authoring model: **start empty, add pieces**\n- forbidden combinations: **none at this level yet**\n- empty/default nodes should expose available features plainly; if that feels wrong later, change it later\n\n## Still open\nThe hard unresolved question is where zoom-revealed surface area lives: how much is a node feature versus how much is environment/semantic-zoom behavior.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": "",
