    {
      "id": "node-primitive-note-migration-policy",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Migration Policy",
      "position": {
        "x": 2905,
        "y": 2264
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Migration Policy\n\nThis item is complete once the migration law is explicit.\n\n## Preferred path\n- document/content nodes should prefer `FixedNode` and `DefaultNode`\n- new work should follow the clarified contract: explicit ports, shared theme/state tokens, editor-owned drag/resize, and declared view surfaces\n\n## Compatibility rule\n- existing custom/operational nodes keep working\n- no forced rewrite just to satisfy the clearer model\n\n## Exception policy\n- operational/integration nodes may stay custom when they have a real reason\n- that is now an intentional exception, not silent drift\n\n## First migration family\n- `FixedNode` document/content family is the canonical first family\n- planning/document-style nodes are aligned enough for now\n\n## Deferred work\n- feral operational nodes remain later consolidation targets, not beta blockers",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
